y, and rebellion. Pasolini’s representations of youth reflected and shaped those ideas.Offering a systematic treatment of youth and adolescence within Pasolini’s eclectic body of work, Fictions of Youth provides both a broad overview of the changing nature of youth within Italian modernity and an in-depth study of Pasolini’s significant contribution to that transformation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAdolescence in literature. 0aFascism in literature. 0aFascism in motion picturesxCriticism, interpretation, etc. 0aFascism in motion pictures. 0aYouth in literature. 0aYouth in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262135040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442621350423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442621350.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles